{"key":"post-11790099","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11790099</id>\n<content>Sterlite and Rubbermaid are the two quality brands.&amp;nbsp; Walmart probably has some crappy made in china totes that are brittle and is why so many people crack them while drilling the holes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Use a sharp drill bit, drill at high speed, and back off on the pressure just as the bit is breaking through the plastic.&amp;nbsp; If you have one of those brittle totes, try putting a light bulb or hair dryer inside for a few minutes to warm it up.&amp;nbsp; That should soften the plastic and help prevent cracking.&amp;nbsp; however, if it cracks, it's no biggie other than looks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Drill holes on all six sides, and elevate the tub on bricks or some other spacer for best results.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Just to correct a technical error above, CO2 does not drain out the bottom.&amp;nbsp; Generally, fresh air enters the bottom, passes through the perlite, and then out the sides and top.&amp;nbsp; The CO2 mixes with the air, thus it exhausts out the sides and top.&amp;nbsp; It's not a separate layer below the air.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11790164</next>\n<prev>11790053</prev>\n<first>11788742</first>\n<last>11790334</last>\n<when>1262986347</when>\n<utime>01/08/10 11:32 PM</utime>\n</post>"}